bug.short_desc: wlfreerdp killed by SIGABRT on any mouse activity
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Description of problem: I attempted to launch wlfreerdp (Wayland version) and connect to a Windows 2016 server. It connects, but the moment that the mouse enters the frame, it dumps core.
Version-Release number of selected component: freerdp-2.0.0-12.20160909git1855e36.fc25
Additional info: reporter: libreport-2.8.0 backtrace_rating: 4 cmdline: /usr/bin/wlfreerdp /v:10.18.25.39 /u:Administrator /d:FEDORATESTING crash_function: wl_abort executable: /usr/bin/wlfreerdp global_pid: 11005 kernel: 4.8.4-301.fc25.x86_64 pkg_fingerprint: 4089 D8F2 FDB1 9C98 pkg_vendor: Fedora Project runlevel: N 5 type: CCpp uid: 13041
Truncated backtrace: Thread no. 1 (9 frames) #2 wl_abort at src/wayland-util.c:418 #3 wl_closure_invoke at src/connection.c:932 #4 dispatch_event at src/wayland-client.c:1310 #5 dispatch_queue at src/wayland-client.c:1456 #6 wl_display_dispatch_queue_pending at src/wayland-client.c:1698 #7 display_dispatch_events at /usr/src/debug/FreeRDP-1855e36179fb197e713d41c4ef93e19cf1f0be2f/uwac/libuwac/uwac-display.c:290 #8 UwacDisplayDispatch at /usr/src/debug/FreeRDP-1855e36179fb197e713d41c4ef93e19cf1f0be2f/uwac/libuwac/uwac-display.c:399 #9 handle_uwac_events at /usr/src/debug/FreeRDP-1855e36179fb197e713d41c4ef93e19cf1f0be2f/client/Wayland/wlfreerdp.c:186 #10 wlfreerdp_run at /usr/src/debug/FreeRDP-1855e36179fb197e713d41c4ef93e19cf1f0be2f/client/Wayland/wlfreerdp.c:268
